cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new approach for classification using limited labeled target data and enormous unlabeled source data. This falls under the domain of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) as the proposed approach is applied to image datasets. The approach involves learning a common space where the conditional distributions over domains remain the same, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of SVM classifiers also suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
